{"title":"Gemma Doyle (politician)","pageID":27322268,"categories":["Living people","1981 births","Labour Co-operative MPs for Scottish constituencies","UK MPs 2010–2015","Female members of the Parliament of the United Kingdom for Scottish constituencies","Members of the Parliament of the United Kingdom for Scottish constituencies","21st-century Scottish women politicians","21st-century Scottish politicians"],"sections":[{"title":"","depth":0,"paragraphs":[{"sentences":[{"text":"Gemma Doyle (born 13 April 1981) is a British former politician who served as Member of Parliament (MP) for West Dunbartonshire from 2010 to 2015.","links":[{"text":"Member of Parliament","type":"internal","page":"Member of Parliament (United Kingdom)"},{"text":"West Dunbartonshire","type":"internal","page":"West Dunbartonshire (UK Parliament constituency)"}],"formatting":{"bold":["Gemma Doyle"]}},{"text":"A member of the Labour and Co-operative parties, she has worked in public affairs since her departure from Parliament.","links":[{"text":"Labour and Co-operative parties","type":"internal","page":"Labour and Co-operative"}]}]}],"templates":[{"description":"British Labour Co-operative politician","bot":"PearBOT 5","template":"short description"},{"date":"August 2021","template":"use dmy dates"},{"list":["Shadow portfolios"],"titlestyle":"border:1px dashed lightgrey","template":"collapsed infobox section begin"},{"template":"collapsed infobox section end"},{"year":"1981","month":"04","day":"13","df":"y","template":"birth date and age"}],"infoboxes":[{"embed":{"text":"yes"},"suboffice1":{"text":"Shadow Minister for Defence Personnel, Welfare and Veterans","links":[{"text":"Shadow Minister for Defence Personnel, Welfare and Veterans","type":"internal","page":"Minister for Defence Personnel, Welfare and Veterans"}]},"subterm1":{"text":"2010–2015"}},{"name":{"text":"Gemma Doyle"},"image":{"text":"File:Gemma-doyle (cropped).jpg"},"caption":{"text":"Doyle in 2015"},"office1":{"text":"Member of Parliament for West Dunbartonshire","links":[{"text":"Member of Parliament","type":"internal","page":"Member of Parliament (United Kingdom)"},{"text":"West Dunbartonshire","type":"internal","page":"West Dunbartonshire (UK Parliament constituency)"}]},"term_start1":{"text":"6 May 2010"},"term_end1":{"text":"30 March 2015"},"predecessor1":{"text":"John McFall","links":[{"text":"John McFall","type":"internal","page":"John McFall, Baron McFall of Alcluith"}]},"successor1":{"text":"Martin Docherty","links":[{"text":"Martin Docherty","type":"internal","page":"Martin Docherty-Hughes"}]},"birth_date":{"text":"April 13, 1981"},"birth_place":{"text":"Alexandria, West Dunbartonshire, Scotland","links":[{"text":"Alexandria","type":"internal","page":"Alexandria, West Dunbartonshire"},{"type":"internal","page":"West Dunbartonshire"}]},"party":{"text":"Labour Co-op","links":[{"text":"Labour Co-op","type":"internal","page":"Labour and Co-operative"}]},"alma_mater":{"text":"University of Glasgow (MA)","links":[{"type":"internal","page":"University of Glasgow"},{"text":"MA","type":"internal","page":"Master of Arts"}]}}]},{"title":"Early life","depth":0,"paragraphs":[{"sentences":[{"text":"Gemma Doyle was born on 13 April 1981 in Alexandria, West Dunbartonshire.","links":[{"text":"Alexandria","type":"internal","page":"Alexandria, West Dunbartonshire"},{"type":"internal","page":"West Dunbartonshire"}]},{"text":"She received a Master of Arts (MA) in European Civilisation from the University of Glasgow.","links":[{"type":"internal","page":"Master of Arts"},{"type":"internal","page":"University of Glasgow"}]}]}],"references":[{"title":"Gemma Doyle {{!}} Senior Managing Director {{!}} FTI Consulting","url":"https://www.fticonsulting.com/experts/gemma-doyle","access-date":"2023-05-20","website":"www.fticonsulting.com","template":"citation","type":"web"},{"url":"http://www.dellam.com/english/ST/STRATHLEVEN%20REGENERATION%20COMPANY%20LIMITED.html","title":"Strathleven Regeneration C.I.C.","publisher":"Dellam Corporate Information","date":"22 June 2011","accessdate":"21 November 2012","template":"citation","type":"web"},{"url":"http://gemmadoyle.org.uk/pages/about-gemma/","title":"About Gemma","publisher":"gemmadoyle.org.uk","accessdate":"21 November 2012","url-status":"dead","archive-url":"https://web.archive.org/web/20120711032232/http://gemmadoyle.org.uk/pages/about-gemma/","archive-date":"11 July 2012","template":"citation","type":"web"}]},{"title":"Political and later career","depth":0,"paragraphs":[{"sentences":[{"text":"Doyle was a researcher for Cathie Craigie, then a Member of Scottish Parliament, and later worked as a Labour Party officer.","links":[{"text":"researcher","type":"internal","page":"researcher"},{"type":"internal","page":"Cathie Craigie"},{"text":"Member of Scottish Parliament","type":"internal","page":"Member of the Scottish Parliament"},{"text":"Labour Party","type":"internal","page":"Labour Party (UK)"}]},{"text":"She has also worked for Holyrood Communications, a political communications company, and the Institution of Civil Engineers.","links":[{"text":"political communications","type":"internal","page":"political communications"},{"type":"internal","page":"Institution of Civil Engineers"}]}]},{"sentences":[{"text":"Following her departure from Parliament, she relocated to London and became director of a public affairs firm.","links":[{"type":"internal","page":"London"}]},{"text":"Doyle has served as a member of the London Labour board and chair of Bermondsey and Old Southwark Labour.","links":[{"type":"internal","page":"London Labour"},{"text":"Bermondsey and Old Southwark","type":"internal","page":"Bermondsey and Old Southwark (UK Parliament constituency)"}]},{"text":"She is a trustee of the Foreign Policy Centre.","links":[{"type":"internal","page":"Foreign Policy Centre"}]}]}],"references":[{"last1":"Warry","first1":"Richard","title":"Election results 2017: How do you get over losing your job as an MP?","publisher":"BBC","url":"https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-39807111","accessdate":"12 October 2017","template":"citation","type":"news"},{"title":"Regional Executive Committee","url":"https://labourinlondon.org.uk/regional-executive-committee/","access-date":"2023-05-20","website":"London Labour","language":"en-GB","template":"citation","type":"web"},{"date":"18 September 2019","title":"Bermondsey Corbynites claim Neil Coyle breached rules in trigger ballots","url":"https://labourlist.org/2019/09/bermondsey-corbynites-claim-neil-coyle-breached-rules-in-trigger-ballots/","accessdate":"23 September 2019","publisher":"LabourList","template":"citation","type":"web"},{"title":"Trustees","url":"https://fpc.org.uk/about/team/trustees/","accessdate":"27 March 2019","publisher":"Foreign Policy Centre","template":"citation","type":"web"}]},{"title":"Parliamentary career","depth":1,"paragraphs":[{"sentences":[{"text":"At the 2004 European Parliament election, she contested the Scotland constituency as a Labour candidate.","links":[{"text":"2004 European Parliament election","type":"internal","page":"2004 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom"},{"text":"Scotland","type":"internal","page":"Scotland (European Parliament constituency)"}]}]},{"sentences":[{"text":"Doyle was elected as Member of Parliament for West Dunbartonshire at the 2010 general election.","links":[{"text":"Member of Parliament","type":"internal","page":"Member of Parliament (United Kingdom)"},{"text":"West Dunbartonshire","type":"internal","page":"West Dunbartonshire (UK Parliament constituency)"},{"text":"2010 general election","type":"internal","page":"2010 United Kingdom general election"}]},{"text":"She served on the Energy and Climate Change Committee and the Administration Committee from July to November 2010.","links":[{"type":"internal","page":"Energy and Climate Change Committee"},{"type":"internal","page":"Administration Committee"}]}]},{"sentences":[{"text":"Following Ed Miliband's election as Labour Leader, Doyle was appointed Shadow Defence Personnel, Welfare and Veterans Minister in October 2010.","links":[{"type":"internal","page":"Ed Miliband"},{"text":"election as Labour Leader","type":"internal","page":"2010 Labour Party leadership election (UK)"}]},{"text":"During her tenure on the opposition front bench, she was a member of the committee scrutinising the Armed Forces Act 2011.","links":[{"type":"internal","page":"Armed Forces Act 2011"}]}]},{"sentences":[{"text":"Doyle was defeated by the Scottish National Party's Martin Docherty at the 2015 general election.","links":[{"type":"internal","page":"Scottish National Party"},{"text":"Martin Docherty","type":"internal","page":"Martin Docherty-Hughes"},{"text":"2015 general election","type":"internal","page":"2015 United Kingdom general election"}]}]}],"references":[{"title":"Gemma Doyle, former MP, West Dunbartonshire – TheyWorkForYou","url":"https://www.theyworkforyou.com/mp/gemma_doyle/west_dunbartonshire","website":"TheyWorkForYou","template":"citation","type":"web"},{"url":"https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-11494915","publisher":"BBC News","title":"Ed Miliband's shadow cabinet and ministerial teams","date":"12 October 2010","template":"citation","type":"news"},{"url":"https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201011/cmselect/cmarmed/779/77901.htm","accessdate":"20 Sep 2013","title":"Select Committee on the Armed Forces Bill","publisher":"parliament.uk","template":"citation","type":"web"}]},{"title":"Personal life","depth":0,"paragraphs":[{"sentences":[{"text":"Doyle has been married to Gregor Poynton, a political strategist and Scottish Labour campaigner.","links":[{"type":"internal","page":"Scottish Labour"}]}]}],"references":[{"last":"Waddell","first":"Lorraine","date":"2013-07-11","title":"West Dunbartonshire MP's husband caught up in Labour scandal","url":"https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/local-news/west-dunbartonshire-mps-husband-caught-2533665","access-date":"2023-05-20","website":"Daily Record","l